Package application

Class Camp

java.lang.Object
application.Camp
public class Camp extends Object
Representation of a camp event. Many-to-Many relation with Student, One-to-Many relation with Staff.
Camps/Events last a certain duration in discrete day(s).
The Users involved can be a Staff-in-Charge, Attendee or Committee Member.
Relations with Students are handled by the Signup class.

  • Constructor Details

    • Camp

      public Camp(int ID, String name, String faculty, LocalDate start, LocalDate end, LocalDate regEnd, String loc, String desc, int maxSlots, int maxComm, String creator, int visible)
      Representation of a Camp in CAMs. Each Camp should be added to the master CampList to be parsed properly in CAMs.
      Parameters:
      ID - Integer ID to be assigned to the Camp. Either derived from the data .csv or by getGlobalIDCounter()
      name - String name to be assigned to the Camp.
      faculty - String of Faculty code that the Camp is designated.
      start - LocalDate of the Start date
      end - LocalDate of the End date
      regEnd - LocalDate of the Registration End date
      loc - String location/venue of the camp
      desc - String description of the camp
      maxSlots - Integer Max Slots of the camp. This count includes Attendee + Committee
      maxComm - Integer of how many of the slots are exclusively for Committee members.
      creator - UserID of the creator of the camp.
      visible - Boolean on whether the camp is visible to students

      public boolean checkClash(LocalDate start1, LocalDate end1)
      Checks for clashes between this camp and another start and end date.
      A Start Date falling on the same day and the other camp's End Date is considered a clash.

      end1 - End date of the other camp.

    • checkCampStatus

      public application.CampStatus checkCampStatus()
      Returns the state that a Camp is in real-time.
      OPEN - Registration date has not passed.
      CLOSED - Registration date has passed, but Start Date has not passed.
      ONGOING - Start Date has passed, but End Date has not passed.
      ENDED - End Date has passed.
      Returns:
      The campStatus of the camp
